</section>

<div class="body">

    <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
    <p class="section-label">How it works</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top 20 submissions win &#8212; here is how to get there</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">No tiers, no first-come-first-served. The top 20 submissions selected by quality each win $250. Submit your first piece through the PartnerStack challenge. Have more to share? You can submit up to three additional pieces &#8212; message us directly through PartnerStack with all of your content URLs.</p>

    <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">01</div>
            <div class="step-title">Pick a topic</div>
            <div class="step-body">Choose autonomous marketing, competitor comparison, or submit one of each.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">02</div>
            <div class="step-title">Create your content</div>
            <div class="step-body">Blog post or YouTube video. Use the playbooks as your guide before you start.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">03</div>
            <div class="step-title">Submit in PartnerStack</div>
            <div class="step-body">Submit your first URL through the challenge in PartnerStack. For additional submissions, message us directly through PartnerStack.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">04</div>
            <div class="step-title">Winners announced</div>
            <div class="step-body">The top 20 are selected by quality. Winners notified directly by July 20, 2026.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">

    <!-- TOPICS -->
    <p class="section-label">Content topics</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Two topics to choose from</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Both topics have a dedicated playbook with everything you need &#8212; positioning, proof points, content ideas, and SEO guidance.</p>

    <div class="topic-grid">
        <div class="topic-card">
            <div class="topic-header blue">
                <div class="topic-eyebrow">Topic one</div>
                <div class="topic-name">Autonomous Marketing</div>
            </div>
            <div class="topic-body">
                <p class="topic-desc">Content about how ActiveCampaign's Active Intelligence and AI Agents make marketing autonomous &#8212; saving time, improving results, and scaling personalization.</p>
                <a class="topic-link" href="https://derrickhernandez-ac.github.io/content-playbooks/autonomousmarketer-playbook.html">View the Autonomous Marketing Playbook &#8594;</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="topic-card">
            <div class="topic-header moss">
                <div class="topic-eyebrow">Topic two</div>
                <div class="topic-name">Competitor Comparison</div>
            </div>
            <div class="topic-body">
                <p class="topic-desc">Content comparing ActiveCampaign against Mailchimp, HubSpot, Klaviyo, Brevo, or Kit &#8212; showing where ActiveCampaign wins and why readers should switch.</p>
                <a class="topic-link" href="https://derrickhernandez-ac.github.io/content-playbooks/competitor-playbook.html">View the Competitor Content Playbook &#8594;</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">

    <!-- REQUIREMENTS -->
    <p class="section-label">Requirements</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What qualifies</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Your submission must meet these minimums to enter judging. Quality is what wins &#8212; the checklist is the floor, not the ceiling.</p>

    <div class="req-grid">
        <div class="req-card">
            <div class="req-card-title">&#128221; Blog post</div>
            <ul class="req-list">
                <li>1,200+ words, original and net-new</li>
                <li>ActiveCampaign and Active Intelligence mentioned by name</li>
                <li>Your affiliate link included</li>
                <li>At least one screenshot or visual</li>
                <li>Affiliate disclosure included</li>
                <li>Published on your own site or LinkedIn</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="req-card">
            <div class="req-card-title">&#127909; YouTube video</div>
            <ul class="req-list">
                <li>Five minutes or longer, original content</li>
                <li>ActiveCampaign and Active Intelligence mentioned</li>
                <li>Affiliate link in video description</li>
                <li>Platform demo or screen recording included</li>
                <li>Affiliate disclosure in description</li>
                <li>Published on your own YouTube channel</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="req-card" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
            <div class="req-card-title">&#128683; What will not qualify</div>
            <ul class="req-list" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:8px 24px;">
                <li class="no">AI-generated content without meaningful human editing</li>
                <li class="no">Plagiarized or repurposed existing content</li>
                <li class="no">Content that does not mention ActiveCampaign</li>
                <li class="no">Pure promotional content with no educational value</li>
                <li class="no">Content published outside the contest window</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout callout-info">
        <strong>How winners are selected</strong>
        <p>All submissions are reviewed by the ActiveCampaign affiliate team. The top 20 are selected based on content quality, depth of coverage, originality, and how well the content serves the reader. Each piece is evaluated independently &#8212; you can submit up to three pieces total to increase your chances. Win two spots and you take home $500.</p>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">

    <!-- TIMELINE -->
    <p class="section-label">Key dates</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Timeline</h2>

    <div class="callout callout-warning">
        <strong>Contest window: May 20 &#8211; June 30, 2026</strong>
        <ul>
